<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-09-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-09-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="92" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d92">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files: Lot 54–D270</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by General <persName type="from">Chou
                                    En-lai</persName> to General <persName type="to">Marshall</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">SM 827</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-09-16">September 16,
                                1946</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear General</hi>: Because of some business that
                            requires my attendance, I am called upon to leave for Shanghai to-day.
                            In case there is any matter that you want to communicate to me, please
                            contact my associates Messrs. Liao Cheng-chih and Wang Ping-nan
                            here.</p>
                        <p>As soon as you have decided to convene the Committee of Three, I will be
                            back on your notice.</p>
                        <p>Faithfully yours,</p>
                        <closer>[Signature in Chinese] <lb/>
                            <signed>(<hi rend="smallcaps">Chou En-lai</hi>)</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>